Assignment

Because this dataset is limited to Human Chromosome 18, ensure you download only the Human Chromosome 18 FASTA and GTF/GFF3 annotation files for your reference genome indexing.
Using the full genome will unnecessarily slow down you.

State the versions and source of your reference and annotation files.
Find out how to subset the the GTF and reference file for chr18 only.

Tools to use - 

1. Quality Control (QC)
Assess the quality of the raw reads.
    Tools: FastQC, MultiQC

2. Read Trimming
Remove adapter sequences and poor-quality base calls.
    Tools: Trimmomatic, Cutadapt, or fastp

3. Genome Alignment
Map the trimmed reads to the human reference genome (Chromsome 18).
    Tools: STAR, HISAT2 or salmon
    You must build a reference index for your aligner before running this step.

4. Alignment QC
Assess the quality of aligned bam files.
    tools: Qualimap, RseqQC, samtools, deeptools

5. Read Quantification
Count how many reads map to each gene/transcript.
    Tools: featureCounts (Subread package) or pseudo-aligners like Salmon / Kallisto.

6. Differential Expression Analysis
Use the generated count matrix to find genes that are differentially expressed between Day 0 and Day 7.
    Tools: DESeq2 or edgeR (in R/RStudio).
    Goal: Identify which genes on Chromosome 18 are significantly up-regulated or down-regulated during the EMT transition.
    Provide your logic for deciding log2FC and padj threshlod. 

7. Pathway and process enrichment
Use the list of significantly up and down regulateed genes for GO terms enrichment and 1) ORA analysis and 2)GSEA analysis for pathway enrichment.
Specify which pathway database you have use.




